<section><h2>Latest release</h2>

<p>The latest and recommended version of Nix is
<strong>[%latestNixVersion%]</strong>, released 11 April 2014. The
quickest way to install it on Linux and Mac OS X is to run the
following in a shell (as a user other than 'root'):

<pre><span class="muted">$</span> bash &lt;(curl <a href="[%root%]nix/install">https://nixos.org/nix/install</a>)</pre>

This script does require that you have <tt>sudo</tt> access to 'root'
(since it needs to create the directory <tt>/nix</tt>). See <a
href="[%nixManual%]#chap-installation">the manual</a> for more
information.</p>

<p>The following are also available:

<ul>

  <li><a href="[%latestNixMirror%]/nix-[%latestNixVersion%].tar.xz">Source tarball</a>.</li>

  <li><a
  href="http://hydra.nixos.org/release/nix/nix-[%latestNixVersion%]">Binary
  packages for several platforms</a>, including RPMs, Debs and binary
  tarballs for Mac OS X.</li>

  <li><a href="[%nixManual%]#ssec-relnotes-[%latestNixVersion%]">Release
  notes</a>.</li>

  <li><a href="[%nixManual%]">Manual</a> (<a
  href="[%latestNixMirror%]/manual.pdf">PDF</a>).  Please read the <a
  href="[%nixManual%]#chap-quick-start">“Quick Start” section of the
  manual</a> for an overview of how to install and use Nix.</li>

</ul>

</p>

</section>


<section><h2>Continuous builds</h2>

<p>You can grab the latest bleeding-edge pre-release from our <a
href="../hydra">continuous build system</a>:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="http://hydra.nixos.org/job/nix/trunk/release#tabs-constituents">The
  latest development release of Nix</a> (<a
  href="http://hydra.nixos.org/job/nix/trunk/release/latest-finished/eval/job/tarball/download-by-type/file/source-dist">source
  tarball</a>, <a href="http://hydra.nixos.org/job/nix/trunk/release/latest-finished/eval/job/tarball/download-by-type/doc/manual">manual</a>, and RPMs and Debs for several platforms)</li>
</ul>

</section>


